ducational content, only 2/3 access it) - Market Drivers & Trends - Target Customer Segments with detailed profiles - Customer Pain Points & Gap Analysis 3. COMPETITIVE LANDSCAPE Create a detailed competitive analysis table with columns: - Competitor Name - Business Model - Key Offerings - Pricing Model - Strengths - Weaknesses - Our Differentiation Include these competitors: - Elsevier Patient Education - WebMD Ignite - Mytonomy - Wolters Kluwer - Nucleus Medical Media - Ghost Productions - XVIVO - Vyond (animation tool) 4. BUSINESS MODEL & VALUE PROPOSITION - Core Value Propositions for each customer segment - Business Model Canvas - Revenue Streams (detailed breakdown) - Unit Economics projection 5. MONETIZATION STRATEGY & PRICING Create a detailed pricing table with 4 tiers: - Starter (Solo Practitioners): $149/month - Professional (Small Clinics): $449/month - Enterprise (Hospitals/Health Systems): $1,499/month - Educational (Medical Schools): $999/month For each tier include: - Target customer - Number of videos included - User licenses - Features included - Annual discount option - Expected input/output/rationale columns 6. TECHNOLOGY STACK & TOOLS (NO-CODE/LOW-CODE FOCUS) Create a detailed implementation table with columns: - Function/Purpose - Recommended Tool - Why This Tool - Pricing - Implementation Complexity - Expected Input - Expected Output Include: VIDEO CREATION TOOLS: - Vyond (medical animation templates) - Descript (AI video editing) - Synthesia (AI avatars for physician presenters) - Canva (graphics/thumbnails) - ElevenLabs (voiceover) PLATFORM & DELIVERY: - Vimeo OTT or Uscreen (video hosting/delivery) - Webflow (website/landing pages) - Airtable (content management database) CUSTOMER MANAGEMENT: - Stripe (payments/subscriptions) - Memberstack or MemberSpace (authentication) - Intercom (customer support) - HubSpot (CRM) ANALYTICS: - Wistia or Vidyard (video analytics) - Google Analytics - Mixpanel (user behavior) 7. CONTENT CREATION FRAMEWORK C