evenue Projections by Customer Segment - Cost Structure Breakdown - Break-even Analysis - Key Financial Metrics (CAC, LTV, LTV:CAC ratio, Gross Margin) 13. OPERATIONAL SOPS Create detailed click-by-click SOPs: SOP 1: \"Onboarding New Healthcare Client\" SOP 2: \"Creating New Medical Explanation Video\" SOP 3: \"Medical Content Validation Process\" SOP 4: \"Customer Support Escalation\" SOP 5: \"Video Analytics Review & Optimization\" Each SOP should have: - Step # - Action Description - System/Tool - Screenshot/Visual Reference Needed - Expected Input - Expected Output - Quality Check - Time Estimate - Responsible Role 14. RISK ANALYSIS & MITIGATION Table format: - Risk Category - Specific Risk - Probability - Impact - Mitigation Strategy - Contingency Plan Categories: - Medical/Legal (HIPAA, medical accuracy, liability) - Market (competition, adoption rates) - Operational (content production speed, quality control) - Financial (cash flow, funding) - Technology (platform reliability, scalability) 15. SUCCESS METRICS & KPIs Create a KPI dashboard table: - Metric Category - Specific KPI - Target (Month 6) - Target (Month 12) - Target (Year 2) - Measurement Method - Review Frequency Categories: - Customer Acquisition - Revenue & Financial - Product Engagement - Content Library - Customer Satisfaction - Operational Efficiency 16. APPENDICES - Glossary of Medical/Healthcare Terms - Sample Video Scripts - Medical Advisory Board Requirements - Legal Compliance Checklist - Technology Integration Diagram DESIGN REQUIREMENTS: - Professional healthcare color scheme (blues, teals, white) - Use modern sans-serif fonts - Include data visualizations where appropriate - Make all tables responsive and easy to read - Add executive summary boxes/callouts for key insights - Use icons for different sections - Include a table of contents at the top with anchor links - Add \"Source\" citations for all market data - Make pricing tables visually prominent with highlighted \"recommended\" tiers - Use color coding for priority levels (high=red, medium=yellow, low=green) IMPORTANT NOTES: - This is for a non-technical founder, so all technical explanations should be clear - Focus heavily on no-code/low-code solutions - Include specific dollar amounts and timeframes - Every recommendation should have rationale/data support - Create this as a working strategic document that can guide actual implementation - Emphasize the \"$9.8B growing to $32.28B\" market opportunity throughout - Reference the 20.1% CAGR medical animation market growth - Mention patient education gap (94% want content, only 67% get it) Excellent! I've created a comprehensive business strategy document for your medical explanation video platform, MedVisual. Let me now create supporting visual assets to make this even more actionable. Using Tool | Programmatic Visualization Create a business model flowchart for MedVisual medical explanation video platform showing: 1. INPUT SOURCES (Left side): - Medical content sources (textbooks, clinical guidelines, physician SMEs) - Target customer segments (clinics, hospitals, physicians, medical students) 2. CORE PLATFORM PROCESSES (Center): - Content Creation Workflow (Medical validation → Script → Animation → Review → Publish) - Video Library Management - Customer Management - Analytics & Optimization 3. REVENUE STREAMS (Right side): - Subscription tiers (Starter $149/mo, Professional $449/mo, Enterprise $1,499/mo, Educational $999/mo) - Custom video creation services - White-label licensing - API access fees 4. VALUE DELIVERY (Bottom): - Patient education improvement - Reduced physician time explaining procedures - Better patient outcomes - Medical student learning enhancement Use a professional healthcare color scheme (blues, teals, greens). Create clear arrows showing the flow from inputs → processes → revenue → value delivery. Make it suitable for investor presentations or internal strategic planning. Title: \"MedVisual Business Model & Value Flow\" Generated Images (3) Generated 10/26/2025, 10:45:37 AM Generated 10/26/2025, 10:45:37 AM Generated 10/26/2025, 10:45:37 AM File Changes (3) medvisual_business_model_flowchart.png /home/user/output/medvisual_business_model_flowchart.png Download 10/26/2025, 10:43:40 AM v1 image/png medvisual_content_customer_workflow.png /home/user/output/medvisual_content_customer_workflow.png Download 10/26/2025, 10:45:14 AM v1 image/png medvisual_implementation_roadmap.png /home/user/output/medvisual_implementation_roadmap.png Download 10/26/2025, 10:44:24 AM v1 image/png Notebook notebook_6hiaQ.ipynb notebook_6hiaQ.ipynb Download 4/15/2026, 12:16:43 PM v1 application/x-ipynb+json Perfect! Now let me view the HTML document to confirm everything is complete: Using Tool | Doc View Viewing document: 1,100 Excellent! Now let me create a Knowledge Base document as requested to track all documents created in this session: Using Tool | Doc Generate Generate content before line 1, instruction: Create a Knowledge Base document titled \"MedVisual Project Knowledge Base\" that organizes all the documents and outputs created in this chat session. Structure: 1. PROJECT OVERVIEW - Project Name: MedVisual Medical Explanation Video Platform - Date Created: October 26, 2025 - Project Type: Healthcare SaaS - Medical Education Video Platform - Business Model: Subscription-based video library for clinics, hospitals, physicians, medical students 2. MARKET OPPORTUNITY SUMMARY - Total Market Size: $9.8B (2024) → $32.28B (2030) at 22.19% CAGR - Medical Animation Subset: $396.2M (2023) → $1.42B (2030) at 20.1% CAGR - Key Gap: 94% patients want educational content, only 67% receive it (27-point gap) - Target Geography: North America (37.66% market share) 3. DOCUMENTS CREATED IN THIS SESSION Create a table with columns: - Document Name - Document Type - Purpose/Description - Key Contents - Status - File Name Include these documents: 1. MedVisual Business Strategy Document (HTML) - Complete strategic busi